### GSAP MorphSVGPlugin: Morph Shapes with Different Points (JavaScript)

Source: https://gsap.com/resources/svg

The MorphSVGPlugin allows you to animate the morphing of SVG path data between shapes with different numbers and types of points. It can also convert other SVG elements to paths for morphing. You can use selector text or elements as input, and optionally control the shape mapping with 'shapeIndex'.

```javascript
gsap.registerPlugin(MorphSVGPlugin);

// Morphing between two paths with different point counts
gsap.to("#myElement", {
  morphSVG: "#path2"
});

// Morphing a rectangle to a path
gsap.to("rect", {
  morphSVG: "#path2"
});

// Converting an element to a path and then morphing
const pathElement = MorphSVGPlugin.convertToPath("#myCircle", {swapArrays: true});
gsap.to(pathElement, {
  morphSVG: "#path2",
  shapeIndex: "-1" // Example of using shapeIndex
});

// Morphing using selector text for the target
gsap.to("#myPath1", {
  morphSVG: "#myPath2",
  duration: 2
});

```

--------------------------------

### Sequence Multiple Morph SVG Animations

Source: https://gsap.com/docs/v3/Plugins/MorphSVGPlugin

Demonstrates how to chain multiple morphing animations sequentially using GSAP's TimelineLite/Max. This example shows a circle morphing into a hippo, then a star, an elephant, and finally back to its original circle shape, with a one-second delay between each morph.

```javascript
tl.to(circle, { duration: 1, morphSVG: "#hippo" }, "+=1")
  .to(circle, { duration: 1, morphSVG: "#star" }, "+=1")
  .to(circle, { duration: 1, morphSVG: "#elephant" }, "+=1")
  .to(circle, { duration: 1, morphSVG: circle }, "+=1");
```

--------------------------------

### Render Morphing Paths to Canvas using GSAP MorphSVG

Source: https://gsap.com/docs/v3/Plugins/MorphSVGPlugin

This example demonstrates how to use the MorphSVG plugin's `render` function to draw morphing SVG paths onto an HTML canvas. It includes setting up the canvas context, defining the drawing function, and animating a morph between two SVG elements.

```javascript
let canvas = document.querySelector("canvas"),
  ctx = canvas.getContext("2d"),
  vw = (canvas.width = window.innerWidth),
  vh = (canvas.height = window.innerHeight);
ctx.fillStyle = "#ccc";
gsap.to("#hippo", {
  duration: 2,
  morphSVG: {
    shape: "#circle",
    render: draw,
  },
});
function draw(rawPath, target) {
  let l, segment, j, i;
  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, vw, vh);
  ctx.beginPath();
  for (j = 0; j < rawPath.length; j++) {
    segment = rawPath[j];
    l = segment.length;
    ctx.moveTo(segment[0], segment[1]);
    for (i = 2; i < l; i += 6) {
      ctx.bezierCurveTo(
        segment[i],
        segment[i + 1],
        segment[i + 2],
        segment[i + 3],
        segment[i + 4],
        segment[i + 5]
      );
    }
    if (segment.closed) {
      ctx.closePath();
    }
  }
  ctx.fill("evenodd");
}
```

--------------------------------

### Minimal MorphSVG Usage

Source: https://gsap.com/docs/v3/Plugins/MorphSVGPlugin

Demonstrates the simplest way to use MorphSVGPlugin to morph one SVG element into another. It targets an element with the ID 'circle' and animates its 'd' attribute to match the shape of the element with the ID 'hippo' over a duration of 1 second. This requires both SVG elements to be present in the DOM.

```javascript
gsap.to("#circle", { duration: 1, morphSVG: "#hippo" });
```

--------------------------------

### Morphing with Map Algorithm

Source: https://gsap.com/docs/v3/Plugins/MorphSVGPlugin

Demonstrates morphing between two SVG elements using the 'map' property to specify the matching algorithm ('complexity'). This can help align segments of paths that might not naturally correspond based on size or position.

```javascript
gsap.to("#id", {
 duration: 1,
 morphSVG: { shape: "#otherID", map: "complexity" },
});
```

